summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing numerous private flight entries and exits for Jeffrey Epstein between December 2016 and December 2018. The document shows extensive international travel, primarily between the U.S. and the Caribbean/Europe, using multiple aircraft tail numbers and passport/document numbers.

keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein made over 130 international flights on private aircraft between December 2016 and December 2018.
Epstein used at least two different passport/document numbers (469911707 and 547017616) during this travel period.
Primary travel routes connected Florida (KPBI, KFXE), New York/New Jersey (KTEB, KISP), the Caribbean (TIST, TFFJ), and Europe (LFPB).
The document shows Epstein was actively traveling internationally in the years leading up to his 2019 arrest.
Multiple private aircraft tail numbers were used: N212JE, N120JE, N415LM, N331JE, and N90JE.
